\subsection{Model support}{

Out of the box:
\itemize{
\item \code{glmmTMB} — hurdle NB2, NB2, Poisson, binomial
\item \code{lme4} — \code{glmerMod} (binomial, Poisson, negative binomial via
\code{glmer.nb}), \code{lmerMod} (Gaussian, for log-transformed indices)
}

For other families, supply a custom extractor; see
\code{vignette("custom-extractor")}.
}

\subsection{Key assumption}{

\code{data} passed to \code{\link[=extract_params]{extract_params()}} \strong{must be a plain \code{data.frame}},
not a tibble or \code{data.table}.  BLUP extraction via \code{ranef()} can
silently fail on non-data-frame inputs.  Call \code{as.data.frame(data)}
first if needed.
}
